                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d33">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Uhl</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Smythe</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-03-07">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 7, 1895</hi>.</date>
                    </dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 82.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to your dispatch No. 122, of the 23d
                    ultimo, you seem to be under a misapprehension as to the date of the
                    naturalization of Bernard Campbell. Mr. Campbell was naturalized in 1876, many
                    years prior to the date on which his claim arose. His naturalization certificate
                    is on file in this Department.</p>
                <p>I desire further to say that the failure to make earlier presentation of the
                    claim was not due to any fault of Mr. Campbell. The reasons for the delay are
                    satisfactory to this Department.</p>
                <p>You have never been authorized to cooperate in the appointment of a claims
                    commission, and the protocol referred to by you must be submitted to this
                    Department before any action is taken under it.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Edwin F. Uhl</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Acting
                            Secretary.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
